FBIS4-12228 "drnes067_g_94001" FBIS-NES-94-067 Daily Report 5 Apr 1994 Sudan Government Forces Control 90 Percent of South Government Forces Control 90 Percent of South EA0604210594 Nairobi KNA in English 1830 GMT 5 Apr 94 EA0604210594 Nairobi KNA English BFN [Text] Khartoum, 5 Apr (KNA/PANA) -- The Sudanese Government controls 90 percent of the territory in the south where a civil war has raged for some years, Mahdi Ibrahim, the director of political affairs in the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, has said. Ibrahim disclosed this when he addressed a political forum in Omdurman Province. He accused a rebel leader, John Garang, of fearing peace in the territory because he did not have any plans for its development.
